  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I also know that in Romania, there were three more children born to my family, which made the family of six, six children.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Four brothers and two sisters, three of them being born in Romania between the years of 1928 and 1933.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in Romania in 1933, the Romanians simply decided that they will not permit Polish citizens, which we were at that time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We obviously didn't emigrate to Romania legally or with permission, so we were illegally there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so at one time, the Romanian authorities came to our house in 1933, and they told us to just take with us what we can carry.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they simply took us to the border of Romania and Poland, someplace in the Stanislavov area or near the area of Lviv.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And took us-- the Romanian soldiers took us to the boundary and pointed to us that-- to the direction of Poland, and this is where we would go.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Naturally, as we crossed the border, the Polish authorities caught onto this family of eight people, six children, two of them practically infants.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the Polish authorities, a Polish policeman, took this whole family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Being a Jewish family had a lot to do with on how we would be treated.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they simply took the family away and threw us into jail.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now, here we were.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We were Polish citizens by right, but yet, the Polish authorities threw us in jail.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I remember distinctly sitting in a jail with a window way up high with, with bars.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I remember being in jail at the age of eight as we came out of Romania.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
